**Definition**
jQuery Mobile is a touch-optimized web framework built on top of jQuery that enables the creation of responsive, mobile-friendly websites and applications using HTML5, CSS, and JavaScript.

**Types**

* Single-page applications (SPA) using jQuery Mobile
* Multi-page mobile web interfaces
* Theme-based UI components

**Working**
jQuery Mobile enhances HTML elements using data-role attributes to automatically create mobile UI widgets such as buttons, dialogs, lists, and navigation. It loads pages dynamically using Ajax and applies consistent theming across devices.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
HTML + jQuery → jQuery Mobile Processing
             → UI Widgets + Transitions
             → Mobile Web Interface
```

**Advantages**

* Easy to build mobile UI using HTML attributes
* Cross-platform compatibility
* Built-in touch events and transitions
* Theming framework for customization

**Disadvantages**

* Slower than modern JS frameworks
* Heavy for large applications
* Limited compared to React/Vue-based mobile apps

**Examples**

```html
<div data-role="page">
  <div data-role="header"><h1>Home</h1></div>
  <div data-role="content">
    <p>Welcome to jQuery Mobile!</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

**Short code snippets**
Include jQuery Mobile:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.css">
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.1.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.4.5/jquery.mobile-1.4.5.min.js"></script>
```

**Applications**

* Mobile websites
* Prototypes for UI/UX
* Lightweight mobile dashboards
* Simple cross-device web apps
